The location is great (ten minute walk from Pike Place Market) but construction in and around the area means you're forced to use valet parking ($25/night).	Only downside is the charge for parking, $27 a night, but that is now standard, if not low, for parking in Seattle.	We found out afterwards that the manager took off the second night room charge and parking from the bill, but the damage has been done.	It was fun to watch all the concert goers before and after the concert - and not to have to worry about parking or showing up early.	There was an online special of $129/night, which included valet parking.